Perfect! Now I can see the current implementation. Looking at the `m2ap_decode_pdu()` function (lines 177-190), I can see the switch statement that needs to be reordered. Currently, the order is:

1. `M2AP_M2AP_PDU_PR_initiatingMessage` (line 178-179) 
2. `M2AP_M2AP_PDU_PR_successfulOutcome` (line 181-182)
3. `M2AP_M2AP_PDU_PR_unsuccessfulOutcome` (line 184-185)

According to the PR description, this causes scheduling priority inversion because `initiatingMessage` (new requests) are processed before `unsuccessfulOutcome` (error responses) and `successfulOutcome` (success responses).

The fix is to reorder these cases to prioritize by:
1. `unsuccessfulOutcome` (highest priority - error responses)
2. `successfulOutcome` (medium priority - success responses)  
3. `initiatingMessage` (lowest priority - new requests)

